  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-21 17:47 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Fear & Greed Signal Fails as a Live Selector\n\n**Task:** Test whether Fear & Greed adds actionable edge to the current enriched PM trade dataset, and check whether it can help select better Polymarket entries right now.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM is flat. Current market scans at 17 UTC show no actionable trade because the bot is outside active hours and observed bias remains below the live `45` threshold.\n- I tested all enriched YES trades with `fg_value` in `confidence_outcomes.jsonl`. The result is blunt: **all 37 enriched trades occurred in Extreme Fear (`fg_value <= 15`)**, with overall WR **62.2% (23/37)**.\n- Because the entire enriched sample sits inside the same F&G bucket, Fear & Greed currently provides **zero discrimination** across trades. It tells us the macro regime has been fear-heavy, but it does **not** separate winners from losers inside the live sample.\n- The real separation still comes from microstructure features, not F&G: `NORMAL` V5b tag is **85.7% WR (6/7)**, `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` is **33.3% WR (1/3)**, and hour quality remains highly uneven (`11h 72.7%`, `12h 70.6%`, `19h 28.6%`).\n- I also checked a simple divergence proxy using BTC vs VWAP during fear. That also failed to become useful because **36 of 37** fear-tagged trades were below VWAP, so it still does not create a meaningful decision boundary.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is actually a good research result, even if it's not the sexy one. F&G looked promising as a macro overlay, but right now it is saturated. When one signal is pinned in the same state for the whole sample, wiring it into confidence scoring is just narrative inflation. The better move is to spend P4 effort on a feature that changes trade to trade, like liquidation bursts, VWAP distance magnitude, or short-term regime acceleration. The alpha is in what moves, not in what stays stuck at Extreme Fear for days.\n\n**Decision:**\n- **Do not wire Fear & Greed into live PM confidence scoring yet.** It is not discriminative enough in the current dataset.\n- Treat F&G as a dashboard/regime context signal only, not as an execution signal.\n- Promote a stronger P4 follow-up: build a **distance-from-VWAP / liquidation burst** feature that changes intra-session and can actually rank entries.\n\n**Next:** Backtest a new P4 feature using enriched trades plus regime/liquidation state: compare WR for entries taken during high liquidation-burst windows and for entries with larger BTC-to-VWAP dislocation. If either beats the current baseline by >5 percentage points, wire that into confidence scoring before reconsidering F&G.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 17:43 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] 19h Session Edge Decay Review\n\n**Task:** Review live PM bot state, recent enriched outcomes, and current session behavior to decide whether the evening window still deserves capital or needs tightening.\n*",
